Each sequence is a chain of subsets A₁ �� A₂ ��... �� A��. Each A_i is a subset of {1,2,...,10}, and each A_{i} is a subset of A_{i+1}. Therefore, the total number of such sequences is the number of chains of subsets of {1,2,...,10} of length from 1 to 10. Each element in the set can be present in the chain starting at some position. For each element, the choice is the position where it enters the chain, which can be from 1 to 10. Therefore, each element has 10 choices, leading to 10^10 total sequences. Therefore, K=10^10.
